TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {31949=2013 Season: Appeared in nine games and made four starts at cornerback during the year…finished the season with 19 total tackles, including 16 solos…was credited with a season high six tackles at Arizona State. 2012 Season: Played in and started the final 10 games of the season...had 33 total tackles with 25 solos during his first season...recorded at least one tackle in each of his games with a season high seven at Eastern Washington...had six tackles with an interception and four pass breakups at Idaho State. 2011 Season: Sat out the season as a redshirt. High School: Graduated from Redlands East Valley HS in 2011…was named to the CIF all-Inland Division and first team all-Citrus Belt League as a senior… tallied 31 tackles as a senior while helping the team to an 8-3 record…the Wildcats won CBL titles his final two seasons…had six interceptions as a senior and 14 during his career to set school records…picked off three passes against Redlands…also earned all-CBL honors in track. Personal: Has yet to declare a major...parents are Robert Armstrong and Naomi Rodriguez.}
